quran[71]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,when the blind man came to him
  80,3,How would you know? Perhaps he might be purified
  80,4,or he might take heed and benefit from the reminder
  80,5,But he who was indifferent
  80,6,you give him your full attention
  80,7,although you are not to be blamed if he does not purify himself
  80,8,"But as for the one who came to you striving [for purification]"
  80,9,and he fears Allah
  80,10,you let yourself to be distracted from him
  80,11,No indeed; this is a reminder –
  80,12,so whoever wills may give heed to it –
  80,13,on venerable pages
  80,14,exalted and purified
  80,15,"[preserved] in the hands of angel-scribes"
  80,16,honorable and obedient
  80,17,Woe to man; how ungrateful he is
  80,18,From what did He create him
  80,19,He created him from a drop of semen and proportioned him
  80,20,then He made the way easy for him
  80,21,then He caused him to die and be buried
  80,22,"then when He wills, He will resurrect him"
  80,23,Yet he has not fulfilled what He commanded him
  80,24,Let man consider the food he eats
  80,25,How We poured down rainwater in torrents
  80,26,"and caused the soil to split open [for sprouts]"
  80,27,and cause grains to grow in it
  80,28,as well as grapes and fodder
  80,29,and olive trees and date palms
  80,30,and dense orchards
  80,31,and fruits and grass
  80,32,as provision for you and your livestock
  80,33,But when the Deafening Blast comes
  80,34,on that Day everyone will flee from his sibling
  80,35,and from his mother and father
  80,36,and from his wife and children
  80,37,"On that day, everyone will have enough concern of his own"
  80,38,"On that Day, some faces will be bright"
  80,39,cheerful and rejoicing
  80,40,while other faces will be dust-stained
  80,41,covered in darkness
  80,42,"Such are the disbelievers, the wicked"
  81,1,When the sun is wrapped up in darkness
  81,2,and when the stars are scattered
  81,3,and when the mountains are vanished
  81,4,and when pregnant camels are left unattended
  81,5,and when wild beasts are gathered
  81,6,and when the seas are set on fire
  81,7,and when the souls are sorted
  81,8,and when the baby girl buried alive is asked
  81,9,for what crime she was killed
  81,10,and when records of deeds are spread open
  81,11,and when the sky is stripped away
  81,12,and when the Blazing Fire is flared up
  81,13,and when Paradise is brought near –
  81,14,then every soul will know what it has brought about
  81,15,I swear by the receding stars
  81,16,that rise and hide
  81,17,and by the night as it departs
  81,18,and by the day as it breaks –
  81,19,"Indeed, this [Qur’an] is a word conveyed by a noble angel-messenger"
  81,20,"extremely powerful, highly revered with the Lord of the Throne"
  81,21,"obeyed [by other angels] and moreover, trustworthy"
  81,22,"Your fellow [the Prophet] is not madman"
  81,23,"He indeed saw him [Gabriel] on the clear horizon"
  81,24,"He does not withhold [knowledge of] the unseen"
  81,25,"This [Qur’an] is not the word of an accursed devil"
  81,26,So which way are you going
  81,27,It is but a reminder to the worlds
  81,28,for those among you who wish to take the straight path
  81,29,"But you cannot wish except by the Will of Allah, the Lord of the worlds"